quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  12,53,"Yet I do not absolve myself, for the human soul is prone to evil, save that on which my Lord has mercy; verily, my Lord is Forgiving, Merciful"
  12,54,"And the king said, \"Bring him (Joseph) to me. I will give him a special position with myself.\" And when he had spoken with him he said, \"Verily, to-day you are with us in a well established place of trust"
  12,55,"He said, \"Place me over the store-house of the land; verily, I will be an expert custodian. (one who is skilled and knows what is required)"
  12,56,"Thus did We establish Joseph in the land that he might possess (settle or control) what part (in the manner, time and place) he pleases. We reach with Our mercy whom We will. We waste not the wages of those who do right"
  12,57,Surely the reward of the Hereafter is better for those who believe and fears (ward off evil or are constant in righteousness)
  12,58,"And his brethren came to Joseph, and they presented themselves unto him and he knew them, but they recognised him not"
  12,59,"And when he had given them their provisions he said, \"Bring me your brother that you have from your father (but different mothers). Do you not see that I give good measure, and that I am the best of hosts"
  12,60,"But if you bring him not to me, no measure shall you have with me, nor shall you come nigh me"
  12,61,"They said, \"We will beg him from our father, and we will surely do it"
  12,62,"Then he said to his servants, \"Put their merchandise (they brought in payment) back into their packs, so that they may discover it only when they have returned to their family; per chance (or possibly) they may return"
  12,63,"And when they returned to their father, they said, \"O our father! A measure is withheld from us; so send with us our brother that we may obtain the measure, and, verily, we will guard him well"
  12,64,"He said, \"Shall I entrust you with him with results other than when I entrusted you with his brother before him? But Allah is the best of keepers, and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful"
  12,65,"And when they opened their packs they found their merchandise restored to them. Said they, \"O our father! What more can we crave? Here are our goods restored to us. We shall get provisions for our folk, and we shall guard our brother, and shall have"
  12,66,"He said, \"I will by no means send him with you until you give me a solemn oath - In the name of Allah that you will surely bring him back to me, unless you are yourselves besieged (made powerless).\" So when they had sworn their oaths he said, &q"
  12,67,"And he said further, \"O my sons! Enter not by one gate, but enter by several gates. Not that I can avail you aught against Allah. Lo! Judgment (decision, command) rests only with Allah. In Him do I put my trust, and on Him do the trusting rely"
  12,68,"And when they had entered as their father bade them, it availed them nothing against (the plan of) Allah. It fulfiled but a want in Jacob´s soul; for, verily, he was possessed of knowledge that We had taught him; but most of mankind know not"
  12,69,"And when they entered into the presence of Joseph, he took his brother to stay with him, and said, \"Verily, I, even I, am your brother, so sorrow not for their doings (past, present and future)"
  12,70,"And when he had given them their provisions, he placed the drinking cup in his brother´s pack; then a crier shouted out, \"O you in the caravan! Verily, you are thieves"
  12,71,"They said, turning to them, \"What is it that you miss"
  12,72,"Said they, \"We miss the goblet of the king, and whoever brings it shall have a camel-load, and I will be bound by it (the promise)"
  12,73,"They said, \"By Allah! You knew we came not to do evil in the land, and that we were not thieves"
  12,74,"They said, \"And what shall be the penalty thereof if you prove to be liars"
  12,75,"They said, \"The recompense thereof is he in whose pack it is found - he shall be the recompense (atonement) thereof (as a bondsman); thus do we recompense the unjust"
  12,76,And he began (searching) their sacks before the sacks of his brother; then he drew it forth from his brother´s sack. Thus did We devise a stratagem for Joseph. He could not take his brother by the king´s law unless Allah willed. We raise by de